[
  {
    "id": "JOB.21.1",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 21,
    "verse": 1,
    "text": "But Job answered and said,",
    "hash": "f65acd19d797e07425b81014a3e7e1e1b687f6c6f777056186616c73f26df942"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.21.2",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 21,
    "verse": 2,
    "text": "Hear diligently my speech, and let this be your consolations.",
    "hash": "283bdb9fd991dfd1b0cd0c7b5ea32aa87c3ab3a9ff087e7a4e2f1a228e409afe"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.21.3",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 21,
    "verse": 3,
    "text": "Suffer me that I may speak; and after that I have spoken, mock on.",
    "hash": "a3af7af8bc80a29a4efefd868bf55c76c05129e805287f6ce0819bc4239a1006"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.21.4",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 21,
    "verse": 4,
    "text": "As for me, {is} my complaint to man? and if {it were so}, why should not my spirit be troubled? {troubled: Heb. shortened?}",
    "hash": "5383a083d17d5ffa2de9b1b07846b05c61b27d02ee96f5c3fe6a7dfdfbfd8779"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.21.5",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 21,
    "verse": 5,
    "text": "Mark me, and be astonished, and lay {your} hand upon {your} mouth. {Mark...: Heb. Look unto me}",
    "hash": "3a4acd7f6355829d210d07f51cfebd9b9f185530040be3fe0efe4ffa294b4513"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.21.6",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 21,
    "verse": 6,
    "text": "Even when I remember I am afraid, and trembling taketh hold on my flesh.",
    "hash": "ab87e92c7f140dd66143438afab76edb5978d3d6287e12aeb4d19b53dde51335"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.21.7",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 21,
    "verse": 7,
    "text": "Wherefore do the wicked live, become old, yea, are mighty in power?",
    "hash": "6f016858041313460676ed222ccbd7a458488bac33789c1c8e44ed5f8de517c6"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.21.8",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 21,
    "verse": 8,
    "text": "Their seed is established in their sight with them, and their offspring before their eyes.",
    "hash": "d63353daba93c7720b381a126e991ebc898c4302e8ed8bf3f0ab3a2b62dbdbb6"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.21.9",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 21,
    "verse": 9,
    "text": "Their houses {are} safe from fear, neither {is} the rod of God upon them. {safe...: Heb. peace from}",
    "hash": "5b005cfeed70550e15777f00eb00da3bdb736acd5c50f9358e3c12d5c486273f"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.21.10",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 21,
    "verse": 10,
    "text": "Their bull gendereth, and faileth not; their cow calveth, and casteth not her calf.",
    "hash": "029401144f5c47c7b24d0f9c331eb061f07d5ba53b69080323896676d8f9e35b"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.21.11",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 21,
    "verse": 11,
    "text": "They send forth their little ones like a flock, and their children dance.",
    "hash": "07f898e5b9c3a7363bf68048054bd458855dc4c8731b2cc7181bc498e3f05f72"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.21.12",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 21,
    "verse": 12,
    "text": "They take the timbrel and harp, and rejoice at the sound of the organ.",
    "hash": "c4df09fc99c62b18bbd04b3637abe5b928532a047f08681ef6bb36f012e9c189"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.21.13",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 21,
    "verse": 13,
    "text": "They spend their days in wealth, and in a moment go down to the grave. {in wealth: or, in mirth}",
    "hash": "46ede312fec877544697c97d29b3e211de90b6b997489d516a5df9e9b2ef62d3"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.21.14",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 21,
    "verse": 14,
    "text": "Therefore they say unto God, Depart from us; for we desire not the knowledge of thy ways.",
    "hash": "ffdcadf6ee3f4c8daf3621574cfd0bd4be2137f0cd670e2b0f66c632eb829f82"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.21.15",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 21,
    "verse": 15,
    "text": "What {is} the Almighty, that we should serve him? and what profit should we have, if we pray unto him?",
    "hash": "85664661af9cdd10a1082af5aab64d1b3f425eef2ff9fa60c4583ff49082b67c"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.21.16",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 21,
    "verse": 16,
    "text": "Lo, their good {is} not in their hand: the counsel of the wicked is far from me.",
    "hash": "3fb6ded9acdf4bd9993e8007f072d63a41fcade0cd763a6d48146592e4be43e5"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.21.17",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 21,
    "verse": 17,
    "text": "How oft is the candle of the wicked put out! and {how oft} cometh their destruction upon them! {God} distributeth sorrows in his anger. {candle: or, lamp}",
    "hash": "d1ab746a89af76444c85467dabf07df2ebea4e70db5b8bcd12b52582226631bf"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.21.18",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 21,
    "verse": 18,
    "text": "They are as stubble before the wind, and as chaff that the storm carrieth away. {carrieth: Heb. stealeth}",
    "hash": "790f2ff92cdcc92f0acade9f61461a36becf823439715ed865622a5ad8029625"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.21.19",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 21,
    "verse": 19,
    "text": "God layeth up his iniquity for his children: he rewardeth him, and he shall know {it}. {his iniquity: that is, the punishment of his iniquity}",
    "hash": "7a983ecb3a00ddce481d6cc9878f6092a7e0e28b2be458889ccde831cc53a955"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.21.20",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 21,
    "verse": 20,
    "text": "His eyes shall see his destruction, and he shall drink of the wrath of the Almighty.",
    "hash": "85501532c6898143ecd4715c9f6008e71e5846777202bc53d4a9690495b6bb5d"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.21.21",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 21,
    "verse": 21,
    "text": "For what pleasure {hath} he in his house after him, when the number of his months is cut off in the midst?",
    "hash": "4d490c04f655dd85dc6d2c238dd568f4f5e6ac51c1e6da881f3a9de46abf7baf"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.21.22",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 21,
    "verse": 22,
    "text": "Shall {any} teach God knowledge? seeing he judgeth those that are high.",
    "hash": "f6a1200fdd37e4638af6a954750f5876f5a2c1c1c3f94c127ddd303b4cc39585"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.21.23",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 21,
    "verse": 23,
    "text": "One dieth in his full strength, being wholly at ease and quiet. {his...: Heb. his very, or, the strength of, his perfection}",
    "hash": "3f016b6574a30dd56be21451fd0524f630734b10115f8493ff6a6e73de76f69a"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.21.24",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 21,
    "verse": 24,
    "text": "His breasts are full of milk, and his bones are moistened with marrow. {breasts: or, milk pails}",
    "hash": "621f5aa67f8ed000ae40f128d9897cae6c0d23d9edc4db9d31ab5929adfca768"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.21.25",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 21,
    "verse": 25,
    "text": "And another dieth in the bitterness of his soul, and never eateth with pleasure.",
    "hash": "d1046e3473df43776ee375e5e09416518b3541edf671dc3af3547e410870f541"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.21.26",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 21,
    "verse": 26,
    "text": "They shall lie down alike in the dust, and the worms shall cover them.",
    "hash": "58758be2c18f1892f3a070dcb3ab444b26ed576e3b6be1331bb934ea484ffadf"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.21.27",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 21,
    "verse": 27,
    "text": "Behold, I know your thoughts, and the devices {which} ye wrongfully imagine against me.",
    "hash": "3d316c645438ef09d7f0e46ce2ed61dcfcaacac67fb2ac9761deb4dea39b9f32"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.21.28",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 21,
    "verse": 28,
    "text": "For ye say, Where {is} the house of the prince? and where {are} the dwelling places of the wicked? {the dwelling...: Heb. the tent of the tabernacles}",
    "hash": "1acbacd252054694dacf85a4d5b1c0b19cca5c1dc071e0101f764b29be3d05e8"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.21.29",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 21,
    "verse": 29,
    "text": "Have ye not asked them that go by the way? and do ye not know their tokens,",
    "hash": "d2f7cc384f5a7776c019465e243a4081d8ac1d53aab05bdf92c43835d7bc26b3"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.21.30",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 21,
    "verse": 30,
    "text": "That the wicked is reserved to the day of destruction? they shall be brought forth to the day of wrath. {wrath: Heb. wraths}",
    "hash": "aa965165d071c403971632599656020231911244f324e533351e46f55730ba11"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.21.31",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 21,
    "verse": 31,
    "text": "Who shall declare his way to his face? and who shall repay him {what} he hath done?",
    "hash": "2a871e568804521407fafad884c7718c6c2704fbf640bef1cb76e690c3ce0902"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.21.32",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 21,
    "verse": 32,
    "text": "Yet shall he be brought to the grave, and shall remain in the tomb. {grave: Heb. graves} {remain...: Heb. watch in the heap}",
    "hash": "7dc43a81e0c12ffe8bed8abd3b7aab2de7ad8387e3a2875104471cfa325c333f"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.21.33",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 21,
    "verse": 33,
    "text": "The clods of the valley shall be sweet unto him, and every man shall draw after him, as {there are} innumerable before him.",
    "hash": "e018bd4bddbdd0b76b1d28ee72ca4cdf25918aa736b4dbbd5336b262a1a57df3"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.21.34",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 21,
    "verse": 34,
    "text": "How then comfort ye me in vain, seeing in your answers there remaineth falsehood? {falsehood: Heb. transgression?}",
    "hash": "2decd2e13eb8473ca07b3008abc843ca1712e7d8a882b6e9a83973d4e67dba6e"
  }
]